Business Brief -- Airgas Inc.:
   Quarterly Net Climbed 37%;
   Lower Interest Costs Cited
For the nine months, earnings increased to $4.9 million,
or 75 cents a share, from $4.1 million, or 67 cents a share.
Earnings were up because of lower interest costs from debt
repayment, lower interest rates and the effect of
cost-reduction programs. Sales increased 7% to $257.4 million
from $240.4 million.